Using super tanks to make Magic Mirrors double as fluid transfer was a fun bit of trickery and all, but it's time to come up with a serious solution.

Ender Tanks are to fluids what Ender Chests are to items - the same server-wide, color coded public channel system and ability to switch them to private channels with a diamond applies. Only with Ender Tanks you apply the diamond to the dial, not the lock.

Speaking of, right click the dial to toggle fluid auto-extraction. If the orange squares are up, it's turned on. Ender Tanks auto-extract at a rate of 100mb/t, although their actual throughput can be much higher if you use GT pumps (or other means) to insert/extract fluids faster.
